Last week, Senator Elizabeth Warren (D-MA) unveiled her proposal for universal childcare in the United States.
It would establish a network of federally funded, locally run childcare centers across the nation.
More than half of Americans now live in childcare “deserts,” according to the Center for American Progress, including significant majorities of rural and Latino families.